President Donald Trump met with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in Jerusalem. Trump visited the Church of the Holy Sepulchre and the Western Wall, becoming the first sitting US president to do so. Trump expressed his deep emotions about the visit and the impact it had on him. Netanyahu welcomed Trump and thanked him for his commitment to Israel's security and future. The visit strengthens the bond between the US and Israel. Trump spoke about the desire for peace in Israel and the shared values of freedom and human dignity between the two countries. He also discussed the importance of defeating violent ideologies and expressed willingness to work closely with Israel to bring greater safety and security to the region.